quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Merciful-to-all
  55,2,taught the Qur'an
  55,3,created man
  55,4,taught him articulate speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon run on precise calculations
  55,6,The stars and the trees submit to Him
  55,7,"The skies, He raised high and has established the balance"
  55,8,That you may not transgress in the balance
  55,9,"but weigh with justice, and do not violate the balance"
  55,10,"The earth, He laid out for all living creatures"
  55,11,"In it are fruits, and date-palms in clusters"
  55,12,And grains on flourishing stems and fragrant plants
  55,13,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,14,"He created Humankind from dry clay, ringing like pottery"
  55,15,And He created the jinn from a fusion of fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,17,He is Lord of the two sunrises and Lord of the two sunsets
  55,18,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,19,"He merged the two seas, converging together"
  55,20,with a barrier they do not over run between them
  55,21,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,22,From out of both comes pearl and coral
  55,23,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,24,"His are all floating objects, raised above the sea like mountain peaks"
  55,25,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,26,Everyone on it is perishing
  55,27,"but forever will remain the Face of your Lord, full of Majesty and Glory"
  55,28,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,29,To Him turn everyone in the heavens and on earth for their needs; and every day He manifests Himself in yet another way
  55,30,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,31,"We will soon attend to your judgment, you burdensome two"
  55,32,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,33,"Jinn and Humankind, if you are able to break through the confines of the heavens and earth, then break through them. You will not break through except with authority"
  55,34,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,35,"A flash of fire and brass will be sent against you, and you will not be helped"
  55,36,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,37,And when the heaven is split open and becomes rose-colored like oil
  55,38,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,39,"On that Day, no human and no jinn will be asked about his sins"
  55,40,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,41,"Those who forced others to reject Our messages, will be known by their marks, and they will be seized by the foreheads and the feet"
  55,42,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,43,"This is Hell, which those who forced others to reject Our messages denied"
  55,44,They will circulate them between fire and scalding water
  55,45,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,46,But for he who feared to be one day in the Presence of his Lord are two Gardens
  55,47,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,48,With shading branches
  55,49,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,50,In them are two flowing springs
  55,51,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,52,and they have pairs of every kind of fruits
  55,53,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,54,"They will be reclining on couches lined with silk brocade, and the fruit of the two Gardens are near at hand"
  55,55,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,56,"In them are creature-mates of modest gaze, untouched before them by man or jinn"
  55,57,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,58,As though they were rubies and coral
  55,59,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,60,Will the reward for goodness be anything but goodness
  55,61,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,62,And beneath them are two other gardens
  55,63,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,64,Dark green
  55,65,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,66,With two gushing springs
  55,67,So which of your Lord's blessings do you both deny
  55,68,"In them are fruits, date-palms and pomegranates"
  55,69,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,70,In them are sweet and lovely creatures
  55,71,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,72,"Hoor, kept close in their pavilions"
  55,73,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,74,Untouched before them by man or jinn
  55,75,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and beautiful fine carpets
  55,77,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, full of Majesty and Glory"